Description: Fragment from the top of a round, domed lid of a vessel, made of a pale pink marl ware covered with a pale grey exterior slip, surmounted with a small U-shaped handle. The fabric contains small inclusions of limestone.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 64, 66 § 61, pl. xxxvi, 86)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.114, p.224, pl.66)
